        <!-- Avoiding AI Waste -->
        <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-indigo-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-indigo-400 pl-4">Avoiding AI Tool Waste</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">The biggest risk isn't choosing the wrong tool — it's accumulating subscriptions you barely use. Here's how to avoid "AI tool sprawl":</p>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-950/10">
            <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Monthly Audit</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Every month, check: which AI tools did I actually use this month? If you haven't opened a tool in 30 days, cancel it. Most can be re-activated if you need them later.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-950/10">
            <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Overlap Check</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Many tools overlap. ChatGPT can do basic image generation, writing, code, and data analysis — potentially replacing 4 specialised tools. Before adding a new tool, ask: can my existing tools do this?</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-950/10">
            <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">ROI Threshold</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Each tool should save you more time/money than it costs. A £50/month tool that saves 5 hours/month at your rate of £40/hour = £200 value. Clear ROI. A £50/month tool that saves 30 minutes? Cancel it.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/20 bg-amber-950/10">
            <p class="text-amber-400 font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Team Adoption</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">A tool only delivers value if people actually use it. If you buy a licence and your team ignores it after week 1, the tool isn't the problem — the workflow integration is. Fix the habit, or drop the tool.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-indigo-500/30 bg-indigo-950/20">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-indigo-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">💡 The 3-Tool Rule</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">Most small businesses need exactly 3 AI tools to see transformative results: one for <strong class="text-white">content creation</strong> (ChatGPT/Claude), one for <strong class="text-white">visual work</strong> (Canva), and one for <strong class="text-white">operations</strong> (automation or meeting transcription). Everything else is nice-to-have. Master these three before adding more.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">AI tools are the great equaliser for small businesses. A one-person company with the right AI stack can produce content, support customers, and operate with the polish of a 20-person team. The key is choosing wisely, integrating deeply, and measuring honestly.</p>

        <!-- Industry-Specific Picks -->
