        <!-- Security & Privacy -->
        <h2 class="text-xl font-light text-indigo-400 mt-10 mb-4 border-l-4 border-indigo-400 pl-4">Security & Privacy: What to Check</h2>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed mb-4">Before feeding business data into any AI tool, verify these points:</p>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-900/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Data Training Policy</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Does the tool use your inputs to train its models? ChatGPT's free tier does (unless you opt out). Business/API tiers don't. Claude doesn't. Always check. If training is on, don't input confidential data.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-900/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Data Residency</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Where is your data processed and stored? For UK businesses, EU/UK data residency is often required by clients and regulations. Cloudflare Workers AI offers regional processing. OpenAI/Anthropic process in the US (adequate jurisdiction).</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-900/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Certifications</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Look for: SOC 2 Type II, ISO 27001, GDPR compliance statement, and privacy impact assessments. Enterprise tiers of major AI tools typically have these. Free tiers may not offer the same guarantees.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="p-4 rounded-xl border border-gray-700 bg-gray-900/30">
            <p class="text-white font-semibold text-sm mb-2">Employee Guidelines</p>
            <p class="text-xs text-gray-400">Create a simple AI usage policy for your team: what data can/can't be input, which tools are approved, and what outputs need human review. Most AI data breaches happen through employees, not hackers.</p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="not-prose my-6 p-5 rounded-xl border border-amber-500/30 bg-amber-950/10">
          <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-amber-400 uppercase tracking-wider mb-2">🔒 Simple Rule</p>
          <p class="text-sm text-gray-300">If you wouldn't email the data to a stranger, don't paste it into a free-tier AI tool. For sensitive data: use business/enterprise tiers with data protection agreements, or self-hosted solutions like Cloudflare Workers AI where data never leaves your infrastructure.</p>
        </div>

        <p class="text-gray-300 leading-relaxed">The AI tools landscape will continue evolving rapidly — but the fundamental categories and evaluation criteria stay the same. Use this guide as your starting framework, update it quarterly as new tools emerge, and always prioritise tools that solve real problems over ones that just sound impressive.</p>

